&lt;li&gt;Engage with local authorities and AHJs to address safety and compliance requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with product design, systems, and quality teams to ensure early integration of compliance requirements into product development cycles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and manage product compliance plans and timelines to align with project milestones.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and maintain technical documentation for certification submissions, including test reports, risk assessments, and declarations of conformity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Qualifications (Required):&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Electrical Engineering, Mechanical Engineering, Materials Science, or a related technical field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience in battery certification, regulatory compliance, or product safety engineering for EV or ESS products.&lt;/li&gt;
